arm_group.description:
if any of followings is identified the participant is regarded as diabetics and will be recruited in this arm;
Fasting Plasma glucose (FPG) level ≥ 7.0 mmol/l (126 mg/dL)
Plasma glucose ≥ 11.1 mmol/l (200 mg/dL) two hours after a 75 g oral glucose load as in a glucose tolerance test
Symptoms of hyperglycemia and casual plasma glucose ≥ 11.1 mmol/l (200 mg/dL)
Glycated hemoglobin (A1C) ≥ 6.5% if any of followings is identified the participant is regarded as pre-diabetics and will be recruited in this arm;
1- FPG levels of 100-125 mg/dl (5.6-6.9 mmol/l). 2-Two-h plasma glucose (2HPP) in the 75 g oral glucose tolerance test of 140-199 mg/dl (7.8- 11.0 mmol/l)
